9 Relating to retired state employees; to amend Section
10 36-27-8.2, as last amended by Act 2025-409, Code of Alabama
11 1975, to further provide for employment authorized for certain
12 retirees of the Employees' Retirement System or Teachers'
13 Retirement System.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. Section 36-27-8.2, as last amended by Act
16 2025-409, 2025 Regular Session, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§36-27-8.2
19 (a) Any individual who is retired under the Employees'
20 Retirement System may perform duties in any capacity,
21 including as an independent contractor, with any employer
22 participating in the Employees' Retirement System or the
23 Teachers' Retirement System without suspension of his or her
24 retirement allowance provided that: (i) the individual is not
25 employed in a permanent full-time capacity; and (ii) the
26 individual's compensation from the employer in calendar year
27 2016 does not exceed thirty thousand dollars ($30,000).
28 Beginning in calendar year 2017, and each calendar year
