41 (b) Any individual serving as an elected official who
42 has retired from the Employees' Retirement System may serve
43 for his or her full compensation in an elected public office
44 with the state, a county, or an incorporated municipality
45 without suspension of retirement benefits;, provided, that
46 under no circumstances shall such an individual participate in
47 or accrue additional benefits under the Teachers' Retirement
48 System or the Employees' Retirement System for that service,
49 and provided that under no circumstances shall an individual
50 whose retirement is based upon service as an elected official
51 continue in or return to the office and receive both pension
52 benefits and salary. Any provision of this subsection to the
53 contrary notwithstanding, a retiree serving as a local elected
54 superintendent of education shall not receive both pension
55 benefits and salary unless his or her compensation as a local
56 elected superintendent of education does not exceed the annual
